<p>
    Scientific Notation on a calculator
</p>

<p class="introduction">
    Physicists must constantly deal with numbers that are either very large or very small.
    They express these numbers in scientific notation.
    Naturally, physicists must add, subtract, multiply, and divide values in scientific notation.
    Doing this on a calculator requires some difficulty.
</p>


<ul class="definition" data-word = 'The scientific notation button'>
    <li>
        When solving scientific notation on a calculator, always use the "Scientific Notation Button."
    </li>
    <li>
        DO NOT try to type out "x 10^__".
        On large problems with many numbers in scientific notation, you are <emph>very</emph>
        likely to make a mistake.
    </li>
    <li>
        On most scientific calculators, the scientific notation button is "EE" and
        appears as "<small>E</small>" on the screen.
    </li>
    <li>
        (On some others, it is written as "EXP")
    </li>
</ul>

