<p class="definition" data-word = 'Negative Exponents on a Calculator'>
    Most calculators have two buttons that look like a negative sign.
    One of them is the button for "minus" and the other is the button
    for "negative."
    When entering a negative exponent in scientific notation,
    you <emph>must</emph> use <strong>negative</strong> button,
    or you will get an error on your calculator.
</p>

