<p class="definition" data-word = 'Raising Scientific Notation to Exponents'>
    When you need to square or cube a number in scientific notation,
    place that number in parentheses:
    <br>
    <br>
    For example, to compute 6 million cubed, type in
    <br>
    (6<small>E</small>6)^3
</p>


